RACE.RACE_TEXT: DEL MAR RACE 1 5F Turf CR: 85. Maiden Special Weight Purse 61000. FOR CALIFORNIA BRED OR CALIFORNIA SIRED MAIDENS, FILLIES AND MARES THREE YEARS OLD AND UPWARD. Three Year Olds, 122 lbs.; Older, 124 lbs. (Non-Starters For A Claiming Price Of $40,000 Or Less In The Last 3 Starts Preferred). (Rail at 12 feet).
RACE.FOOTNOTES: COME JOIN THE BAND sped to the front and crossed over to the inside, roused at the top of the stretch and remained clear under right handed encouragement. SHE'S NOT KIDDING stalked on the inside and steadied slightly early when COME JOIN THE BRAND cut in front, continued along the rail behind the leader and inside a rival, got boxed in with nowhere to go on the turn, came out and bumped SAND TO SEA in upper stretch and finished willingly for second. SAND TO SEA came away fast while breaking outward, stalked outside a rival into and around the bend, got bumped by SHE'S NOT KIDDING in upper stretch and went evenly late. SATOSHI tracked two wide into the turn, raced three wide turning for home and lacked a rally. IN HER PRYME broke a step slow, chased between rivals three wide into the turn, exited the bend four wide and failed to menace. PLUM CREEK raced three deep at the back, raced four wide into the turn, angled to the rail around the bend and came up empty. THERE WAS A STEWARDS' INQUIRY INVOLVING THE RUNNING OF THE STRETCH RUN BETWEEN SHE'S NOT KIDDING AND SAND TO SEA. AFTER A REVIEW, THE STEWARDS RULED THAT THE INCIDENT DID NOT WARRANT A DISQUALIFICATION AND THERE WOULD BE NO CHANGE.

ENTRY.COMMENT: stalked inside, boxed in turn, came out/bumped upper

FOR THREE YEAR OLDS AND UPWARD WHICH HAVE NEVER WON $18,000 THREE TIMES OTHER THAN MAIDEN, CLAIMING, OR STARTER, OR STATE BRED OR WHICH HAVE NOT WON $65,000 TWICE SINCE JULY 7 OR WHICH HAVE NEVER WON FOUR RACES OR CLAIMING PRICE $100,000. Three Year Olds, 122 lbs.; Older, 124 lbs. Non-winners Of Two Races Since August 25 Allowed 2 lbs. A Race Since Then Allowed 4 lbs. Claiming Price $100,000 (Maiden, Claiming, And Starter Races For $62,500 Or Less Not Considered) (Non-Starters For A Claiming Price Of $25, 000 Or Less In The Last 3 Starts Preferred).
RACE.FOOTNOTES: C Z ROCKET broke a step slow, stalked off the rail, went three wide around the turn, got floated out to the four path leaving the bend, rallied to the front with a sixteenth remaining and drove clear. GOOD WITH PEOPLE closest in pursuit up the backstretch, bid inside PEACEFUL WATERS outside the five-sixteenths pole and quickly took over, cleared that rival entering the stretch, led to midstretch and yielded to C Z ROCKET in deep stretch. PEACEFUL WATERS took control early and showed the way two wide into the turn, challenged near the five-sixteenths pole and offered little resistance to GOOD WITH PEOPLE and relinquished command shortly after, chased three wide into the lane and kept on to secure the show. KINGDOM HEART chased along the inside to the stretch and lacked a rally. ARHAM climbed between rivals then off the rail, navigated the bend three then four wide and weakened.

ENTRY.NAME: Good With People
ENTRY.OWNER: Robison J Kirk and Robison Judy

ENTRY.NAME: C Z Rocket
ENTRY.OWNER: Altamira Racing Stable Madaket Stables LLC and Kagele Tom

RACE.FOOTNOTES: PAULLIAC (IRE) stalked from inside, tipped out into the lane, bid outside the leader with a furlong remaining, took over midstretch, edged away from CASTLEKNOCK and held well over the runner-up. MARS ON FIRE broke a bit slow, tracked on the inside, saved ground through the turn, moved out a bit in the lane, rallied and gaining to the wire. EDDIE'S LAST settled in range, went to wide into the turn, angled four wide into the stretch, finished well from outside and gained third. CASTLEKNOCK closest in pursuit two wide into and around the bend, spun three wide into the stretch, put in a bid at the eighth pole but faltered in deep stretch. HABEAS had good early speed to take control from inside, set the pace through the turn, ridden along a bit off the rail into the stretch, challenged by outer rivals at the eighth pole, lost command midstretch and weakened. RAHM off a bit slow to begin, trailed along the rail then two wide on the turn and was not a factor.

RACE.RACE_TEXT: DEL MAR RACE 4 1M Dirt CR: 84. Claiming Purse 24000. FOR THREE YEAR OLDS AND UPWARD WHICH HAVE NEVER WON TWO RACES. Three Year Olds, 122 lbs.; Older, 125 lbs. Claiming Price $16,000, if for $14,000, allowed 2 lbs.
RACE.FOOTNOTES: NOBLE UNION chased five then four wide on the clubhouse turn, remained four wide through the second bend, rallied in deep stretch and won the bob over TIZ TOK on the line. TIZ TOK tracked three wide early, bid three deep leaving the backstretch, vied outside rivals on the far turn then dueled late on the bend, inched ahead in upper stretch, put away TAHOE SECRETS in deep stretch but then had to fight with NOBLE UNION late and lost the bob at the wire. TAHOE SECRETS away quickly from outside, pressed four then three wide on the clubhouse turn, lost contact with the leader at the half-mile pole, challenged between rivals into the far turn, took over midway around the bend, dueled past the quarter pole in the two path inside TIZ TOK, lost command at the top of the lane, fought back from inside then flattened to third in the final sixteenth. JIMMY THE BOOT chased in the two path then moved inside, began to pull leaving the clubhouse turn and early on the backstretch, chased along the rail then tipped three wide into the drive and finished evenly late. TAKE CHARGE CURLY traveled along the inside, two wide into the far turn, steered out and came four wide into the stretch but lacked further response. ALL THE KING'S MEN grabbed the early lead and led three then two wide on the clubhouse turn, cleared outer rival at the half-mile pole, pressured by a pair of rivals leaving the backstretch, lost command at the five-sixteenths pole, could not keep pace with outer rivals late on the bend and faded down the lane.

ENTRY.OWNER: Goodwin Kelley and Goodwin Timothy Wayne

ENTRY.COMMENT: away quickly, pressed 4-3wide, bid between, led, flattened

RACE.FOOTNOTES: SIGNORA MINISTER stalked briefly then went up to press from outside, dueled past the half-mile pole, put away inner rival at the three furlong marker, met the bid from BIG POND at the five-sixteenths pole, shook free at the quarter pole and remained clear through the lane under a drive. BIG POND bumped with inner rival at the start, stalked off the rail, put in a mild bid at the five-sixteenths pole but could not sustain the challenge approaching the quarter pole, continued three wide in pursuit into the lane and finished willingly for a second best. KRISTI'S TIGER bumped with BIG POND leaving the gate, trailed up the backstretch, went four wide into the turn, continued at the rear now six wide exiting the bend, showed a mild response to urging and got up for third. SATIN DOLL chased three then four wide, could not make any headway in the final furlong and was edged for the show honors. POWER SURGE stalked up the backstretch, coaxed along two wide on the turn then cut the corner into the lane and weakened. R SWIRVIN GIRVIN sent clear from inside then dueled with the winner, failed to keep up at the three-eighths pole, gave way on the turn and tired.

RACE.RACE_TEXT: Seabiscuit H. - Grade2 DEL MAR RACE 7 1 1/16M Turf CR: 108. Stakes Purse 200000. FOR THREE-YEAR-OLDS AND UPWARD. By subscription of $200 each to accompany the nomination, Closed Thursday November 16,2023 with 15 or by supplementary nomination of $2,000 each by noon on Sunday, November 19, $3,000 additional to start, with $200,000 Guar anteed, of which $120,000 to the winner, $40,000 to second, $24,000 to third, $12,000 to fourth and $4,000 to fifth. Weights Sunday, November 19. High weights preferred. A trophy will be presented to the winning owner. (Rail at 12 feet). to the winning owner. (Rail at 12 feet).
RACE.FOOTNOTES: EASTER (FR) broke a step slow, moved inside and became rank when reserved in the early going, continued to tug the rider along in the middle stages, saved ground through the far turn, had to pause momentarily when running up behind rivals in upper stretch, tipped out and surged alongside HONG KONG HARRY (IRE) and edged past late. HONG KONG HARRY (IRE) stalked from inside out of range, drew closer continuing to save ground on the far turn, ridden along into the stretch, tipped out and challenged the leader with a furlong left to run, took over entering the final sixteenth but got outkicked by the winner. BALNIKHOV (IRE) steered to the inside racing at the back, stayed along the fence to the stretch, angled out and put in a late run to gain the show honors. SUMTER stepped to the front along the inside, opened up a comfortable lead in the middle stages, held a diminished lead still clear of the field entering the lane, confronted by HONG KONG HARRY (IRE) with a furlong left to run, relinquished the lead to that rival and weakened in deep stretch. ASTRONOMER rated in the two path outside a rival, chased three wide into the drive, moved out and lacked a bid. CABO SPIRIT closest in pursuit to the far turn, cut into the lead around that bend, took aim two wide entering the stretch but lacked the needed response. YES THIS TIME raced in the two path near the back, traveled three wide turning for home and failed to menace. FRONT RUN THE FED raced outside a rival off the pace, remained two wide to the stretch and could not make an impact.

BUILT DIFFERENT rank early between rivals into the first turn, got bumped from outside at the five-eighths pole, chased two wide through the far turn and flattened out.
